reviews.review_text: Bringing me down, I'm running aground It was clear things were amiss with Jerry on this leg of the summer tour. This show starts off promising but during So Many Roads it is clear Jerry is struggling. They  rebound nicely with a Tom Thumbs and BTW that are quite amazing. The second set is better with Jerry delivering the goods post space. WTGH is spot on and then some subtle interplay amoung the  band, you can  hear a Black Peter tease maybe Wheel too. Jerry raises to the occasion with a very strong SOTM, there was a cresent in the sky this night too. It was my only time at RFK and it was a crazy scene, but very enjoyable.Sound quality is  excellent.

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Set 1 Highlights: Nice openers. Peppy Bertha and Wang Dang Doodle. Vince really cranks up the organ as Jerry attends to some rig issues. Pretty tragic So Many Roads, but Jerry kicks it into gear for the outro. Phil brings it back together with an excellent Tom Thumb's Blues. Kind of a lackluster first set in comparison to the previous shows of this tour. 

Set 2 HIGHlights: Can a cool drums intro improve Victim or the Crime? Nice Eyes, but Bobby is out of tune for most of the song. Samson is very nice. Space>Way To Go Home is pretty cool. SOTM and Brokedown to sooth my soul. Decent 2nd set, but no big highlights for me. Onward to Deer Creek!
